ils**\\n\\nI think the versions could be undesirable, but the project likely doesn't have a Bill of Materials (BOM) associated with it. It's interesting to think about what implications that could have. If there's no BOM, it might cause issues with tracking or assessing components, right? I wonder how the user feels about that — if that's something they were aware of. Overall, I should keep this in mind moving forward!\\n\\n**Evaluating Gradle dependencies**\\n\\nI’m exploring how to set up my Gradle configuration using `testImplementation(\\\"io.quarkus:quarkus-junit-config:$libraryVersion\\\")`. I need to consider creating a sanitized jar from the original resolved file and replace it in the test classpath. It seems I might need to adjust compile classpath too and think about transitive dependencies when excluding modules. I wonder if excluding the root module would also exclude its transitive dependencies or not. I should organize all these points clearly!\\n\\n**Configuring native-image plugin**\\n\\nI’m looking into how the native-image plugin utilizes `runtimeClasspath`, and I should consider excluding `quarkus-junit-config` this way: \\n\\n``` \\nconfigurations.testRuntimeClasspath {\\n  exclude group: 'io.quarkus', module:'quarkus-junit-config'\\n} \\n```\\n\\nBut then I wonder about transitive dependencies — they might still come through the `compileClasspath`. Excluding only the module doesn't automatically exclude transitive ones. I might lean toward filtering with `tasks.withType(Test)` to clean up the classpath, ensuring `graalvmNative` is appropriately set up. I should search for examples to confirm my approach!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_083345cb143e1fb40169fbbbe26aec819eb0b72f97cd09fa82\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-7v5At4hwJsWHybfEb11UIhSKX6tJZNWToHOZGQYkUjd9kE2799FdPjvIfov0p6T590Vh9LBSbtFMCuNmZTzWsC0XH2miJ1yoPWSQoi20SeGoeLcLKofMBZ0QVXKpAQV0K1bq949q7uiDopeIOO8Hv-coS7aOmHFzA_hLpUKaz9MZFT